'''Nikola Moro''' ({{IPA|it|nǐkola môːro|hr}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=eF1gUBk%3D&keyword=II|title=Nìkola|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|accessdate=21 March 2020|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=e1hlWRI%3D&keyword=moro|title=mȏro|quote=Mȏro|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|access-date=21 March 2020|language=hr}}</ref> born 12 March 1998) is a Croatian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Bologna}} club [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
===Dinamo Zagreb===
Aged six, he started football, moving to [[Zagreb]] aged 11.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/kapetan-nikola-moro-navijac-hajduka-a-svim-srcem-igra-za-dinamo-1034099|first=Robert|last=Junaci|title=Kapetan Nikola Moro: Navijač Hajduka, a svim srcem igra za Dinamo|website=[[Večernji list]]|date=30 October 2015|access-date=12 August 2025|language=hr}}</ref> A [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]] fan in his early days in [[Solin]],<ref name="auto"/> Nikola's father Miro yearned for him to contemplate a career at the [[HNK Hajduk Split Reserves and Academy|Hajduk academy]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/nogomet/nikola-zar-si-moro-otac-modre-zvijezde-pustio-sam-sina-u-dinamo-jer-nisam-imao-novca-za-uzdrzavanje-a-u-hajduku-nam-nisu-dali-ni-opremu/5479467/|title=Nikola, Zar Si Mor'o? Otac modre zvijezde: 'Pustio sam sina u Dinamo jer nisam imao novca za uzdržavanje, a u Hajduku nam nisu dali ni opremu'|website=[[Jutarnji list]]|date=8 January 2017|language=hr}}</ref> but he went to the [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb Academy|Dinamo Zagreb academy]] instead. Nikola joined the senior [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] team from the youth academy in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jutarnji.hr/sport/nogomet/novi-dragulj-potpisao-za-dinamo-na-tri-godine-nikola-moro-je-buducnost-modrih/875422/ |title=Novi Dragulj Potpisao za Dinamo na Tri Godine 'Nikola Moro je budućnost Modrih'|website=Jutarnji list|date=18 March 2014 |access-date=24 November 2016}}</ref>

Moro played a full 90 minutes in his [[2015–16 Croatian First Football League|league]] debut for his senior team versus [[NK Lokomotiva Zagreb|Lokomotiva]] in May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/hr/match/lokomotiva-zagreb-vs-dinamo-zagreb/2042800/report |title=Lokomotiva Zagreb 0–4 Dinamo Zagreb izvještaj s utakmice 14.05.2016. 1. HNL |language=hr|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=14 May 2016|access-date=24 November 2016}}</ref> He made his [[2016–17 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut on 7 December, in a 2–0 away defeat to [[Juventus FC|Juventus]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Tironi|first=Hrvoje|date=11 December 2019|title=Moro večeras 100. put u dresu Dinama, izjednačio se s Lukom|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/moro-veceras-100-put-u-dresu-dinama-izjednacio-se-s-lukom-664610|access-date=9 August 2020|website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]]|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=7 December 2016|title=Juventus rutinski i drugi put pobijedio Dinamo|url=https://sport.hrt.hr/364103/liga-prvaka-juventus-dinamo|access-date=9 August 2020|website=[[Croatian radiotelevision]]|language=hr}}</ref> On 22 February 2017, he signed a new contract until 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/future-stars-of-croatia-locked-into-deals-until-2022/|title=Future Stars of Croatia Locked into Deals Until 2022|website=Croatia Week|date=22 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportarena.hr/nogomet/hrvatska/dinamo/lovren-fiolic-i-moro-ostaju/|title=Kako Se Kladiti na Nogomet {{!}} Vodič za Klađenje 2021|website=Sport Arena|access-date=12 August 2025|language=hr}}</ref>

On 27 March 2018, in an international match against [[Moldova national under-21 football team|Moldova U21]], he suffered a severe injury after [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|tearing]] his [[anterior cruciate ligament]].<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Tolić|first1=Josip|last2=Tironi|first2=Hrvoje|date=27 March 2018|title=Stravična ozljeda! Nikoli Mori pukli prednji križni ligamenti...|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/gotova-sezona-nikola-moro-pretrpio-je-stravicnu-ozljedu-566496|access-date=9 August 2020|website=24sata|language=hr}}</ref> He came back to the team on 26 September for the [[2018–19 Croatian Football Cup|Croatian Cup]] game against {{ill|HNK Sloga Mravince|hr|lt=Sloga Mravince}}.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Tironi|first=Hrvoje|date=25 September 2018|title=Nikola Moro se vraća u Mravincima, Dinamo s najjačim sastavom|url=https://www.goal.com/hr/vijesti/dinamo-sloga-mravince-nikola-moro/1k2wl7yafs5201c2sramdwof5b|access-date=9 August 2020|website=Goal|language=hr}} {{Dead link|date=August 2025}}</ref> He made his [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] debut on 14 February 2019 in a 2–1 away defeat against [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 February 2019|title=Foto, Video: Dinamo Poveo Nakon Majstorije Petkovića I Olma, A Onda Je Uslijedio Potpuni Preokret Viktorije Modri izgubili nakon propusta u obrani|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/foto-video-dinamo-poveo-nakon-majstorije-petkovica-i-olma-a-onda-je-uslijedio-potpuni-preokret-viktorije-modri-izgubili-nakon-propusta-u-obrani-8378840|access-date=9 August 2020|website=Sportske novosti|agency=[[Croatian News Agency]]|language=hr}}</ref>

On 6 November, in a decisive [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] home match against [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]], he was [[Sent off (association football)|sent off]] in the 74th minute with Shakhtar scoring a late equalizer for 3–3 to deny Dinamo a direct qualification for the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|knockout phase]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Lazić|first=Petar|date=6 November 2019|title=Dinamo Prokockao Istorijsku Pobedu! Feliks Brih opet najomraženiji čovek na stadionu, ali se sada Srbi raduju!|url=https://sport.blic.rs/fudbal/evropski-fudbal/dinamo-zagreb-sahtjor-liga-sampiona-drama/f9rlnhd|access-date=9 August 2020|website=Blic|language=sr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Starešinčić|first=Danijel|date=23 October 2019|title=Ključnu utakmicu za proljeće u Ligi prvaka Dinamo igra na Maksimiru; zbog ovog mu igra samo pobjeda|url=https://www.tportal.hr/sport/clanak/kljucnu-utakmicu-za-proljece-u-ligi-prvaka-dinamo-igra-na-maksimiru-evo-zasto-mu-igra-samo-pobjeda-foto-20191022|access-date=9 August 2020|website=Tportal.hr|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=11 December 2019|title=ŠAHTAR - ATALANTA 0:3 Nevjerojatna utakmica kojom je Dinamo ispao iz Europe|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2139552|access-date=9 August 2020|website=Index.hr|language=hr}}</ref>

===Dynamo Moscow===
On 17 August 2020, Moro signed a five-year contract with [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web|website=[[FC Dynamo Moscow]]|url=https://fcdynamo.ru/news/events/?id_4=15635|script-title=ru:Никола Моро – в "Динамо"!|date=17 August 2020|language=ru}}</ref> He made his debut two days later in a 2–0 victory against [[FC Rostov|Rostov]], coming on for [[Daniil Fomin]] in the 69th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|date=19 August 2020|title=Eurogolčina Nikole Vlašića u velikom ruskom derbiju protiv Lovrena! Moro debitirao u Moskvi|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/eurogolcina-nikole-vlasica-u-velikom-ruskom-derbiju-protiv-lovrena-moro-debitirao-u-moskvi-15014410|access-date=12 August 2025|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Sokolov|first=Ivan|date=19 August 2020|script-title=ja:Никола Моро дебютировал за "Динамо"|url=https://www.championat.com/football/news-4111279-nikola-moro-debjutiroval-za-dinamo.html|access-date=12 August 2025|website=Championat|language=ru}}</ref> On 18 October, he scored his first goal for the club as Dynamo lost 3–1 against [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=18 October 2020|title=Nikola Moro majstorski zabio prvijenac za moskovski Dinamo, njegova momčad izgubila u derbiju od Vlašića|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/nogomet-mix/nikola-moro-majstorski-zabio-prvijenac-za-moskovski-dinamo-njegova-momcad-izgubila-u-derbiju-od-vlasica-15026096|access-date=12 August 2025|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr}}</ref>

===Bologna===
On 29 August 2022, Moro joined [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] in Italy on loan until the end of the 2022–23 season, with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite press release|website=Bologna FC 1909|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/nikola-moro-al-bologna/|title=Nikola Moro al Bologna|date=29 August 2022|access-date=29 August 2022|language=it}}</ref> On 2 July 2023, Bologna activated the buy option and made his transfer permanent.<ref>{{Cite press release|website=Bologna FC 1909|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/moro-esercitata-lopzione-per-lacquisto-a-titolo-definitivo/|title=Moro, esercitata l'opzione per l'acquisto a titolo definitivo|date=2 July 2023|language=it}}</ref>

==International career==
Representing Croatia at U16, [[Croatia national under-17 football team|U17]], and [[Croatia national under-19 football team|U19]] levels, Moro made the [[2015 FIFA U-17 World Cup#Quarter-finals|quarter-finals]] of the [[2015 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] – eventually losing against [[Mali national under-17 football team|Mali]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.croatiaweek.com/photos-croatia-u-17s-return-home-to-warm-welcome/ |title=Photos: Croatia U-17s Return Home to Warm Welcome|website=Croatia Week |date=5 November 2015|access-date=24 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/u17worldcup/news/y=2015/m=10/news=all-action-moro-gets-his-reward-2721294.html|title=All-action Moro gets his reward|publisher=[[FIFA]]|date=1 November 2016|access-date=24 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151025132203/http://www.fifa.com/u17worldcup/news/y=2015/m=10/news=all-action-moro-gets-his-reward-2721294.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=25 October 2015}}</ref> He also represented [[Croatia national under-21 football team|Croatia U21]] at the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2019]] and [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2021 UEFA Under-21 Euros]],<ref>{{Cite web|date=6 June 2019|title=Gračan objavio konačni popis za U-21 EP|url=https://hns-cff.hr/news/20093/gracan-objavio-konacni-popis-za-ep-u-21/|access-date=21 September 2021|publisher=[[Croatian Football Federation]]|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Kajtazi Roth|first=Anita|date=9 March 2021|title=Bišćan objavio popis igrača za U-21 Euro: Na njemu najviše igrača Dinama i neka nova imena|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rukomet-2021/biscan-objavio-popis-igraca-za-u-21-euro-na-njemu-najvise-igraca-dinama-i-neka-nova-imena---643144.html|access-date=21 September 2021|website=gol.dnevnik.hr|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=17 May 2021|title=Bišćan objavio popis za U-21 Euro: Pozvao i sjajnog mladog hajdukovca|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/biscan-objavio-popis-za-u-21-euro-pozvao-i-sjajnog-mladog-hajdukovca---652149.html|access-date=21 September 2021|website=gol.dnevnik.hr|agency=Croatian News Agency|language=hr}}</ref> [[Captain (association football)|captaining]] the team to the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship#Quarter-finals|quarter-finals of the latter tournament]] for the first time in their history.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Janković|first=Željko|date=25 May 2021|title=Moro: Sad je važno jer su svi glavom na moru...|url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/moro-sad-je-vazno-jer-su-svi-glavom-na-moru-1495287|access-date=21 September 2021|website=[[Večernji list]]|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Olivari|first=Davorin|date=31 May 2021|title=Ispred mladih Vatrenih je najteži mogući ispit! Igor Bišćan ne želi otkriti sastav za sudar s Furijom|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/ispred-mladih-vatrenih-je-najtezi-moguci-ispit-igor-biscan-ne-zeli-otkriti-sastav-za-sudar-s-furijom-15077175|access-date=21 September 2021|website=[[Sportske novosti]]|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=31 May 2021|title=Dramatična borba za polufinale Europskog prvenstva: Hrvatska pala tek u produžecima|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/hrvatska-nije-uspjela-proci-u-polufinale-europskog-prvenstva-za-mlade---653977.html|access-date=21 September 2021|website=gol.dnevnik.hr|language=hr}}</ref>

On 17 May 2021, Moro was named in the preliminary 34-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2020]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/popis-hrvatske-za-euro-2020-ovo-je-26-vatrenih-koji-putuju-na-europsko-prvenstvo---652063.html |title=Dalić objavio popis za Euro 2020: Poznato svih 26 imena, izbornik objasnio iznenađenje|website=gol.dnevnik.hr|date=17 May 2021 |access-date=21 December 2022|language=hr}}</ref> but did not make the [[UEFA Euro 2020 squads#Croatia|final 26]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/zlatko-dalic-potvrdio-popis-26-igraca-za-europsko-prvenstvo-2020---654181.html |title=Sada je konačno: Dalić potvrdio popis od 26 igrača za Euro 2020 |website=gol.dnevnik.hr|agency=Croatian News Agency|date=1 June 2021|access-date=21 December 2022|language=hr}}</ref> He earned his first call-up to the [[Croatia national football team|senior Croatia team]] on 16 August 2021, ahead of the September [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Russia national football team|Russia]], [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] and [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Olivari|first=Davorin|date=17 August 2021|title=Bio je kapetan mlade Hrvatske, a sad je napokon među Vatrenima: 'Tata je najsretniji čovjek na svijetu!'|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/bio-je-kapetan-mlade-hrvatske-a-sad-je-napokon-medu-vatrenima-tata-je-najsretniji-covjek-na-svijetu-15095393|access-date=21 September 2021|website=[[Sportske novosti]]|language=hr}}</ref> However, Moro did not debut until 29 March 2022, when he made an appearance in a 2–1 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] victory against [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 March 2022 |title=Nikola Moro debitirao je za reprezentaciju u prijateljskoj utakmici protiv Bugarske |url=https://telesport.telegram.hr/na-prvu/nikola-moro-debitirao-je-za-reprezentaciju-u-prijateljskoj-utakmici-protiv-bugarske/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220329163744/https://telesport.telegram.hr/na-prvu/nikola-moro-debitirao-je-za-reprezentaciju-u-prijateljskoj-utakmici-protiv-bugarske/ |archive-date=29 March 2022 |access-date=3 April 2022 |website=Telesport |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=29 March 2022|title=Video: Hrvatska preokretom pobijedila Bugarsku na krilima Andreja Kramarića! |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/hrvatska-bugarska-prijenos-opet-u-ranom-terminu-poznat-sastav---716475.html |access-date=3 April 2022 |website=gol.dnevnik.hr|language=hr}}</ref>

